title: Badgers football: Jacob Maxwell, Natrell Jamerson out against Nebraska
title_page: Badgers football: Jacob Maxwell, Natrell Jamerson out against Nebraska
maintext:
University of Wisconsin offensive lineman Jacob Maxwell (shoulder) and cornerback/kickoff returner Natrell Jamerson (leg) will miss Saturdayâ€™s game against Nebraska at Camp Randall Stadium. Both were listed as questionable this week.
Redshirt freshman David Edwards, who split time with Maxwell over the past two games, will make his first career start at right tackle. The Badgers moved Edwards from tight end to tackle this fall.
Jamerson has been out since suffering his injury in Week 2 against Akron.
Redshirt freshman Jon Dietzen will start at left guard Saturday, with Michael Deiter shifting over to center. Brett Connors will not start after doing so the past four games.
